    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A gem cut named for its creator, Vincenzio Peruzzi, a 17th century Venetian lapidary. He applied a brilliant form of cutting, i.e. with 56 facets, a table and a culet. It was seen as an improvement over the earlier Mazarin cut.</Note_Text>
